Hi,

Am I correct in assuming that the JDBC_DRIVER setting is going to be 
unchanged during the lifetime of a crawl? If that assumption is 
correct, then:

1. The Key field should be marked with @Immutable, to prevent 
operators from changing it during an active crawl.
2. Your JDBCWriterProcessor should implement Initializable.
3. The Initializable.initialTasks method should retrieve the value 
and do something useful with it. I imagine your inititalTasks will 
look something like:

public void initialTasks(StateProvider global) {
String driver = global.get(this, JDBC_DRIVER);
String url = global.get(this, JDBC_URL);
String user = global.get(this, JDBC_USER);
String password = global.get(this, JDBC_PASSWORD);
this.dataSource = new SomeDataSourceClass(driver, url, user, 
password);
}

The initialTasks method will be called by the framework when it loads 
a global configuration.

If the driver information can change during a crawl, then you 
probably want your module to also implement the KeyChangeListener 
interface, and replace the dataSource with the new information during 
the KeyChangedEvent.

-Paul

